The Swiss foreign ministry supports LTTE's willingness to negotiate and calls for peace talks to resume promptly.
They advocate for a federal structure in a united Sri Lanka and endorse Norway's role as a facilitator.
The Tamil Tigers are preparing for peace talks in Switzerland after a tour to garner support for rebel self-rule proposals.
Factional fighting and internecine clashes hinder peace negotiations, with accusations of government collusion.
Efforts to revive talks have been stalled since April, prompting Japanese envoy Yasushi Akashi to push for their resumption and address issues like child soldier recruitment.
